<!-- Hint Mode -->
<section id="hint-mode" class="docs-section">
  <h2>ðŸŽ¯ Hint Mode</h2>
  <p>
    Click links, buttons, and interactive elements without using the
    mouse.
  </p>

  <h3>Using Hint Mode</h3>
  <div class="keybinding-list">
    <div class="keybinding-item">
      <kbd>f</kbd>
      <span
        >Enter hint mode - shows letter hints on clickable
        elements</span
      >
    </div>
    <div class="keybinding-item">
      <kbd>a-z</kbd>
      <span>Type hint characters to narrow down selection</span>
    </div>
    <div class="keybinding-item">
      <kbd>Enter</kbd>
      <span>Click the selected element</span>
    </div>
    <div class="keybinding-item">
      <kbd>Backspace</kbd>
      <span>Delete last character or exit hint mode</span>
    </div>
    <div class="keybinding-item">
      <kbd>Esc</kbd>
      <span>Exit hint mode without clicking</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Hint Targets</h3>
  <p>Hint mode automatically detects and highlights:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Links (<code>&lt;a&gt;</code> elements)</li>
    <li>Buttons (<code>&lt;button&gt;</code> elements)</li>
    <li>Form inputs (input, select, textarea)</li>
    <li>Clickable elements with click handlers</li>
    <li>
      Elements with <code>role="button"</code> or
      <code>tabindex</code>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="docs-tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> Hint characters are case-insensitive. Type
    partial hints to filter - you don't always need to complete the
    full hint sequence.
  </div>
</section>